You do have to pay to get into the zoo (or have a membership) to get to the Waterhole Cafe. The toilets at main entrance (free access) are gendered except for the accessible toilet.

name: Northwoods Outfitters
directions: Go in towards the checkout counter and head right, all the way back by the snowboards. There's an unsigned single occupancy bathroom (the only one I've ever used) and a male/female signed one beside it. The unsigned one has a small sink, a toilet and sometimes infrequently stocked supplies. It is the very definition of 'water closet'. Door lock and handle like in most houses.
comment: These are probably the most used restrooms in town, as Northwoods Outfitters has a coffee shop in the front with free WiFi.

name: Indian Hill Trading Post/Shop n' Save
directions: Bathrooms are in the supermarket side. Find the wine, follow the freezers back to the far back corner. There's a small hallway behind the freezers at the back of the store where the bathrooms are. There are three - two 'family' bathrooms and one male/female signed one on the end, all single occupancy. The family bathrooms are handicap accessible with changing tables; the male/female one on the end lacks these amenities and is slightly smaller. Lever type door handles with a flip lock above that shows Vacant/In use outside the bathroom.
comment: In my opinion and limited research, these are your best bathroom options in Greenville due to overall cleanliness, and being in a supermarket

name: Harvest Moon Deli
directions: Harvest Moon Deli is in a strip mall to the side of the Hannaford, parallel with Route 2. The bathroom is literally straight back through the front door. Door handle is a lever type with a twist lock, similar to what you might find in a home, so you don't need a key. There's often a small line during busy times.
comment: I don't know if you need to be a paying customer but you do need to walk past the counter. The food is good though. :)
